         <abstract>
            <p><foreign xml:lang="gez">Dǝrsāna Gabrǝʾel</foreign> is a collection of 12 monthly readings in honour of <persName ref="PRS4377Gabriel"/>, beginning with the
               month of <foreign xml:lang="gez">Tāḫśāś</foreign> (cf. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Samuel2005EAEDersanaGabreel"/></bibl>). Each section usually includes at least one homily, one miracle, one
               commemorative note concerning the apparition of the Archangel to a biblical or a saintly figure, and a <foreign xml:lang="gez">salām</foreign>-hymn to
               <persName ref="PRS4377Gabriel"/> or to other saints or another rhyming strophe in honour of Gabriel, and may also be preceded by a rhyming preamble.
               In some manuscripts, like <ref type="mss" corresp="BAVet82"/>, the <foreign xml:lang="gez">Dǝrsāna Gabrǝʾel</foreign> is divided into 7 readings, one for each
               weekday, and the miracles are grouped separately.
            </p>
         </abstract>
